<paragraph lastPageNumber="32" pageNumber="31">
This monotypic genus is widely distributed in the Amazon basin and in the Essequibo River drainage. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:876EF99C-F1AC-463C-A724-07F74EA691D1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Limatulichthys Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen 1979:88, 91" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Limatulichthys</taxonomicName>
is a sand dweller. As suggested by the hypertrophied development of lower lip in males, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:876EF99C-F1AC-463C-A724-07F74EA691D1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Limatulichthys Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen 1979:88, 91" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Limatulichthys</taxonomicName>
may be a lip brooder like many representatives of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BBF2B074-F3CF-4B98-AE21-BBC93DF8E554" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricariichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Loricariichthys Bleeker 1862:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Loricariichthys</taxonomicName>
group. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
&amp; Nijssen (1976b) revised 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:38F573B1-8A6B-4BF2-A343-8EE95EE94C82" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudoloricaria Bleeker 1862:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudoloricaria Bleeker, 1862</taxonomicName>
, in which they assigned two species: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laeviuscula">P. laeviuscula (Valenciennes, 1840)</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">P. punctata (Regan, 1904)</taxonomicName>
, and designated a lectotype for the latter from BMNH 1893.4.24: 18, described by Regan (1904) as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
&amp; Nijssen (1976b) also put 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:792A9ADC-CC5D-4B8A-BD58-759351DA9361" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Loricaria griseus Eigenmann 1909:8" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">Loricaria griseus Eigenmann, 1909</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EDFCCA09-1315-4024-BD16-C8DBC562C597" authority="Bleeker, 1862" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Rhineloricaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rhineloricaria petleyi Fowler 1940:243" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petleyi">Rhineloricaria petleyi Fowler, 1940</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7B0770A7-61D6-40DD-A6B6-27AA418F35AA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricariichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Loricariichthys parnahybae Fowler 1941:161" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parnahybae">Loricariichthys parnahybae Fowler, 1941</taxonomicName>
into the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudoloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Pseudoloricaria punctata (Regan, 1904)</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
&amp; Nijssen (1976b: p. 125) wrote: “Kner (1854b: 281) published a manuscript name 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">“Loricaria punctata Natterer”</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duodecimalis">“Ancistrus duodecimalis?” (Valenciennes)</taxonomicName>
. Since this name fails to satisfy the provisions in article 11(d) of the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (1964), therefore 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A98A9889-E05C-42E9-807A-86628AF473AD" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Loricaria punctata Regan 1904:285" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata" subGenus="Pseudoloricaria">Loricaria (Pseudoloricaria) punctata Regan, 1904</taxonomicName>
is not subject to the Law of Homonymy”. According to Ferraris (2003) 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Regan, 1904</taxonomicName>
constitutes a primary homonymy of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Kner (ex Natterer), 1854</taxonomicName>
, a representative of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7FD237CE-B4BB-4BB0-A6CB-39DE7205DE74" authority="Weber, 1991" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1991" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Glyptoperichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Glyptoperichthys Weber 1991:639" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Glyptoperichthys</taxonomicName>
. However, it appears that Kner (1854) does not refer to Natterer’s manuscript for a description of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata</taxonomicName>
, but only to a specimen (number 87) recorded in Natterer’s field notes and identified as a representative of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:35063369-E231-4E03-A49C-EE29CD36526F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ancistrus Kner 1854:272" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ancistrus</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, according to articles 11.5, 11.6, and 12.3 of the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature 
<pageStartToken pageNumber="32">(</pageStartToken>
ICZN, 1999), the name 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Kner</taxonomicName>
is not made available. Later, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1864) refers to Kner’s work using the name 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata</taxonomicName>
as an available name in a new combination 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E10B8541-A8C1-4531-BBB2-D70D6A156318" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pterygoplichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pterygoplichthys punctatus Günther &amp; Kner 1864:251" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">Pterygoplichthys punctatus</taxonomicName>
. Acording to ICZN article 11.5.2, referring to an unavailable name does not make it available by its mere citation. Consequently, this species name is hereby new and has to be considered as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E10B8541-A8C1-4531-BBB2-D70D6A156318" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pterygoplichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pterygoplichthys punctatus Günther &amp; Kner 1864:251" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
Pterygoplichthys punctatus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
, 1864
</taxonomicName>
. Steindachner (1881) used the name “ 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Chaetostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">Chaetostomus punctatus sp. Gthr</taxonomicName>
.” and redescribed the species without taking into account the name 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, the new species described as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata</taxonomicName>
by Regan (1904) is not a homonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Kner</taxonomicName>
(1854). Regan (1904) also confirmed the status of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E10B8541-A8C1-4531-BBB2-D70D6A156318" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pterygoplichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pterygoplichthys punctatus Günther &amp; Kner 1864:251" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
Pterygoplichthys punctatus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
, 1864
</taxonomicName>
. Conversely, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isbrùcker">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
</normalizedToken>
(1980) considered that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1864) validated the name 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Natterer, 1854</taxonomicName>
by authorship to Natterer. However, the name 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Natterer</taxonomicName>
is not available as seen previously. Moreover, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1864) published the description of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E10B8541-A8C1-4531-BBB2-D70D6A156318" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pterygoplichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pterygoplichthys punctatus Günther &amp; Kner 1864:251" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">Pterygoplichthys punctatus</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Natterer</taxonomicName>
listed as junior synonym. Considering ICZN article 11.6, the name 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Natterer</taxonomicName>
is not available. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
et al. (2001) accepted the primary homonymy between 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">L. punctata Natterer</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">L. punctata Regan</taxonomicName>
, considered 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">Limatulichthys griseus (Eigenmann, 1909)</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species, and therefore established 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petleyi">Limatulichthys petleyi (Fowler, 1940)</taxonomicName>
as a substitution name for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">Limatulichthys punctatus (Regan, 1904)</taxonomicName>
. Ferraris (2003) considered 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petleyi">L. petleyi</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">L. griseus</taxonomicName>
and also established the latter as a substitution name for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">L. punctata</taxonomicName>
. The nomenclatural status of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:876EF99C-F1AC-463C-A724-07F74EA691D1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Limatulichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Limatulichthys Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen 1979:88, 91" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Limatulichthys</taxonomicName>
remains unclear and this case should be submitted to the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature in order to rule on the validity of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctata">Loricaria punctata Regan, 1904</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
